.TH "FONTFACE.DESCENTOVERRIDE" "3JS" "August 5, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
FontFace.descentOverride \- FontFace: descentOverride property
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]descentOverride\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]FontFace\f[R] interface returns and sets the value of the
\f[CR]\(atfont\-face/descent\-override\f[R] descriptor.
The possible values are \f[CR]normal\f[R], indicating that the metric
used should be obtained from the font file, or a percentage.
.SH VALUE
A string.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[B]let\f[R] fontFace = \f[B]new\f[R] FontFace(
  \(dqRoboto\(dq,
  \(aqurl(\(dqhttps://fonts.example.com/roboto.woff2\(dq)\(aq,
  { descentOverride: \(dq90%\(dq },
);
console.log(fontFace.descentOverride); \f[I]// 90%\f[R]
fontFace.descentOverride = \(dqnormal\(dq;
console.log(fontFace.descentOverride); \f[I]// \(aqnormal\(aq\f[R]
.EE
